text"},{"parameters":{"subject":"=🚨 {{ $json.workflow }} failed at {{ $json.failedNode }}: {{ $json.errorMessage ","bodyContent":"=🚨 {{ $json.workflow }} failed at {{ $json.failedNode }}: {{ $json.errorMessage }}","toRecipients":"={{ $json.email || 'ops@company.com' }}","additionalFields":{}},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.microsoftOutlook","typeVersion":2,"position":[8802,1420],"id":"1c85d6c9-1c51-488e-bec4-15179a167662","name":"Escalate Failure to Outlook","retryOnFail":true,"maxTries":3,"waitBetweenTries":2000},{"parameters":{"operation":"append","documentId":{"__rl":true,"mode":"list","value":"","cachedResultName":"Task Tracker"},"sheetName":{"__rl":true,"mode":"name","value":"Main","cachedResultName":"Main"},"columns":{"mappingMode":"autoMapInputData","value":{},"matchingColumns":[],"schema":[]},"options":{}},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.googleSheets","typeVersion":4.7,"position":[9126,1420],"id":"5d1626a3-8f0a-4d95-83b9-ff51f4c80876","name":"Park in Dead-Letter Queue","retryOnFail":true,"maxTries":3,"waitBetweenTries":2000},{"parameters":{"content":"### New Task Form Submission\n\nServes an n8n-hosted form (Title, Assignee, Duedate). Each submission becomes one execution.\n\nNext: Keep Valid Tasks","width":280,"height":232,"color":5},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote","typeVersion":1,"position":[-330,520],"id":"5ecf68b0-8971-37ed-3c9d-ab9e8e07aab1","name":"Note: New Task Form Submission"},{"parameters":{"content":"### Keep Valid Tasks\n\nDrops items that fail the condition; only qualifying items continue (no false branch).\n\nNext: Prepare Approval Packet","width":280,"height":232,"color":7},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote","typeVersion":1,"position":[-6,520],"id":"2a7d72ac-57b4-5034-56f9-37290fc9ce18","name":"Note: Keep Valid Tasks"},{"parameters":{"content":"### Prepare Approval Packet\n\nShapes the item: writes `requestId`, `summary`, `requestedBy`. Keeps the schema explicit between stages.\n\nNext: Request Approval via Slack","width":280,"height":232,"color":7},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote","typeVersion":1,"position":[318,520],"id":"1f9f880f-dfd3-576e-fde9-a639888e5303","name":"Note: Prepare Approval Packet"},{"parameters":{"content":"### Request Approval via Slack\n\nslack — `action` operation against the connected account.\n\nPorts: ①→ Hold for Decision · ②→ Capture Failure Context\n\n↻ retries 3×/2s · ⚠ failures exit via the error rail · 🔑 Slack OAuth2","width":280,"height":232,"color":2},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote","typeVersion":1,"position":[642,520],"id":"16a46f8b-f034-20fd-6898-b3e118270be8","name":"Note: Request Approval via Slack"},{"parameters":{"content":"### Hold for Decision\n\nPauses the execution until the resume webhook is called — this is the approval/HITL gate.\n\nNext: Approved?","width":280,"height":232,"color":2},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote","typeVersion":1,"position":[966,520],"id":"8da0f6b5-bde1-c307-fda3-65acd7675ed3","name":"Note: Hold for Decision"},{"parameters":{"content":"### Approved?\n\nTwo-way gate on `={{ $json.body?.decision || $json.decision }}`. TRUE continues the happy path, FALSE takes the alternate branch.\n\nPorts: ①→ Execute Approved Action (API) · ②→ Record Decline + Notify Requester","width":280,"height":232,"color":2},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote","typeVersion":1,"position":[1290,520],"id":"3ba54b78-4599-6eda-c41e-3b45947aa209","name":"Note: Approved?"},{"parameters":{"content":"### Execute Approved Action (API)\n\nPOST https://api.example.com/v1/tasks — retries 3× with backoff on failure.\n\nPorts: ①→ Join Decision Paths · ②→ Capture Failure Context\n\n↻ retries 3×/2s · ⚠ failures exit via the error rail · 🔑 API key / bearer for the target API","width":280,"height":232,"color":2},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote","typeVersion":1,"position":[1614,280],"id":"9c8568db-d72f-adaf-2f39-837b078ebdf2","name":"Note: Execute Approved Action (API)"},{"parameters":{"content":"### Record Decline + Notify Requester\n\nslack — `action` operation against the connected account.\n\nPorts: ①→ Join Decision Paths · ②→ Capture Failure Context\n\n↻ retries 3×/2s · ⚠ failures exit via the error rail · 🔑 Slack OAuth2","width":280,"height":232,"color":2},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote","typeVersion":1,"position":[1938,880],"id":"e2906316-141c-f32a-f608-e8b1671d185a","name":"Note: Record Decline + Notify Requester"},{"parameters":{"content":"### Join Decision Paths\n\nRejoins 2 branches into one stream (mode: append) so downstream logic runs once.\n\nNext: Fingerprint for Idempotency","width":280,"height":232,"color":7},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote","typeVersion":1,"position":[2586,520],"id":"81c6debb-4d88-aa8a-ada2-9576e1756148","name":"Note: Join Decision Paths"},{"parameters":{"content":"### Fingerprint for Idempotency\n\nCustom JavaScript: Build a stable idempotency key per task (djb2 hash, no deps)\n\nNext: Drop Already-Processed Items","width":280,"height":232,"color":7},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote","typeVersion":1,"position":[3558,520],"id":"adea9da9-ca64-d7dd-d4b9-a370bf636731","name":"Note: Fingerprint for Idempotency"},{"parameters":{"content":"### Drop Already-Processed Items\n\nCross-execution dedupe: remembers keys it has processed before and drops repeats — the idempotency guard.\n\nNext: Offload to Post-Process Sub-workflow","width":280,"height":232,"color":2},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote","typeVersion":1,"position":[3882,520],"id":"5c665566-f7a5-315a-2f8f-eb0706bc83b5","name":"Note: Drop Already-Processed Items"},{"parameters":{"content":"### Offload to Post-Process Sub-workflow\n\nDelegates to a reusable sub-workflow (single-responsibility building block) and waits for its result.\n\nPorts: ①→ Record Sub-workflow Result · ②→ Capture Failure Context\n\n↻ retries 3×/2s · ⚠ failures exit via the error rail","width":280,"height":232,"color":2},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote","typeVersion":1,"position":[4206,520],"id":"09daed64-b1ff-ec2b-3f49-8d221a0e80eb","name":"Note: Offload to Post-Process Sub-workflow"},{"parameters":{"content":"### Record Sub-workflow Result\n\nSaves key fields onto the execution record — searchable later in n8n's execution list.\n\nNext: Stamp Completion Time","width":280,"height":232,"color":7},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote","typeVersion":1,"position":[4530,520],"id":"1c3ab04e-f450-6503-aec4-77787fb84aa1","name":"Note: Record Sub-workflow Result"},{"parameters":{"content":"### Stamp Completion Time\n\nStamps `completedAt` with the current time for auditing.\n\nNext: Persist Run Metadata","width":280,"height":232,"color":7},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote","typeVersion":1,"position":[4854,520],"id":"c0bf4fb6-883e-8928-40b5-40cb2924a71d","name":"Note: Stamp Completion Time"},{"parameters":{"content":"### Persist Run Metadata\n\nSaves key fields onto the execution record — searchable later in n8n's execution list.\n\nNext: Enrich with Reference Data","width":280,"height":232,"color":7},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote","typeVersion":1,"position":[5178,520],"id":"d36daa7b-01fc-fc92-f7fe-339f46fa73d1","name":"Note: Persist Run Metadata"},{"parameters":{"content":"### Enrich with Reference Data\n\nGET https://enrichment.example.com/v2/lookup — retries 3× with backoff on failure.\n\nPorts: ①→ Fold In Enrichment Fields · ②→ Capture Failure Context\n\n↻ retries 3×/2s · ⚠ failures exit via the error rail · 🔑 API key / bearer for the target API","width":280,"height":232,"color":2},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote","typeVersion":1,"position":[5502,520],"id":"bac40b5c-69ff-2f3c-53a8-3c70e33e0992","name":"Note: Enrich with Reference Data"},{"parameters":{"content":"### Fold In Enrichment Fields\n\nShapes the item: writes `enrichedAt`, `enrichmentSource`. Keeps the schema explicit between stages.\n\nNext: Load Previous Snapshot","width":280,"height":232,"color":7},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote","typeVersion":1,"position":[5826,520],"id":"c2fddd93-beab-f590-ad60-8b20eaee6872","name":"Note: Fold In Enrichment Fields"},{"parameters":{"content":"### Load Previous Snapshot\n\nnotion — `getAll` operation against the connected account.\n\nPorts: ①→ Compute Drift vs Snapshot · ②→ Capture Failure Context\n\n↻ retries 3×/2s · ⚠ failures exit via the error rail · 🔑 Notion integration token","width":280,"height":232,"color":2},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote","typeVersion":1,"position":[6150,520],"id":"ad369b2a-f101-a0a9-c355-cbec3259c8ad","name":"Note: Load Previous Snapshot"},{"parameters":{"content":"### Compute Drift vs Snapshot\n\nCustom JavaScript: Compare current metrics with the previous snapshot\n\nNext: Serialize Run Output (CSV)","width":280,"height":232,"color":7},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote","typeVersion":1,"position":[6474,520],"id":"f5b53207-dd09-b957-b73f-f97ead31b4c4","name":"Note: Compute Drift vs Snapshot"},{"parameters":{"content":"### Serialize Run Output (CSV)\n\nSerializes items to a CSV binary file.\n\nNext: Archive Row Snapshot","width":280,"height":232,"color":2},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote","typeVersion":1,"position":[6798,520],"id":"6eb3cdc4-2714-7527-e2f5-0c5a4e02b003","name":"Note: Serialize Run Output (CSV)"},{"parameters":{"content":"### Archive Row Snapshot\n\ngoogleSheets — `append` operation against the connected account.\n\nPorts: ①→ Tag Pipeline Metadata · ②→ Capture Failure Context\n\n↻ retries 3×/2s · ⚠ failures exit via the error rail · 🔑 Google OAuth2 / service account","width":280,"height":232,"color":2},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote","typeVersion":1,"position":[7122,520],"id":"0e33c1de-5804-a57a-3498-170b659af686","name":"Note: Archive Row Snapshot"},{"parameters":{"content":"### Tag Pipeline Metadata\n\nShapes the item: writes `pipeline`, `version`. Keeps the schema explicit between stages.\n\nNext: Guard Non-Empty title","width":280,"height":232,"color":7},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote","typeVersion":1,"position":[7446,520],"id":"befbcd6d-9510-d8c3-e185-1bd19ea61f95","name":"Note: Tag Pipeline Metadata"},{"parameters":{"content":"### Guard Non-Empty title\n\nDrops items that fail the condition; only qualifying items continue (no false branch).\n\nNext: Cap Batch Volume","width":280,"height":232,"color":7},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote","typeVersion":1,"position":[7770,520],"id":"d5e8630b-2b5c-8670-8b19-e7d4dfbd8807","name":"Note: Guard Non-Empty title"},{"parameters":{"content":"### Cap Batch Volume\n\nCaps the stream at 100 items to protect downstream quotas.\n\nNext: Summarize Run Stats","width":280,"height":232,"color":7},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote","typeVersion":1,"position":[8094,520],"id":"842659bf-3fdf-faf6-2fe3-b6aab30b7423","name":"Note: Cap Batch Volume"},{"parameters":{"content":"### Summarize Run Stats\n\nShapes the item: writes `runAt`, `itemCount`, `status`. Keeps the schema explicit between stages.\n\nNext: Append Audit Row (Google Sheets)","width":280,"height":232,"color":7},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote","typeVersion":1,"position":[8418,520],"id":"93ffff13-ecb3-f45c-4f37-48cb274fd787","name":"Note: Summarize Run Stats"},{"parameters":{"content":"### Append Audit Row (Google Sheets)\n\ngoogleSheets — `append` operation against the connected account.\n\nPorts: ①→ Send Summary to Slack · ②→ Capture Failure Context\n\n↻ retries 3×/2s · ⚠ failures exit via the error rail · 🔑 Google OAuth2 / service account","width":280,"height":232,"color":2},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote","typeVersion":1,"position":[8742,520],"id":"a9b27f13-805c-22fb-6bc0-2b8210b1079a","name":"Note: Append Audit Row (Google Sheets)"},{"parameters":{"content":"### Send Summary to Slack\n\nslack — `action` operation against the connected account.\n\n↻ retries 3×/2s · ⚠ failures exit via the error rail · 🔑 Slack OAuth2","width":280,"height":232,"color":4},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote","typeVersion":1,"position":[9066,520],"id":"5c35e8de-6681-d271-570d-16179475554c","name":"Note: Send Summary to Slack"},{"parameters":{"content":"### Capture Failure Context\n\nShapes the item: writes `failedNode`, `errorMessage`, `workflow`. Keeps the schema explicit between stages.\n\nNext: Escalate Failure to Outlook","width":280,"height":232,"color":3},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote","typeVersion":1,"position":[8418,1540],"id":"cd6d8e82-529b-65fa-bf26-a847f3134177","name":"Note: Capture Failure Context"},{"parameters":{"content":"### Escalate Failure to Outlook\n\nmicrosoftOutlook — `action` operation against the connected account.\n\nNext: Park in Dead-Letter Queue\n\n↻ retries 3×/2s · 🔑 Microsoft OAuth2","width":280,"height":232,"color":3},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote","typeVersion":1,"position":[8742,1540],"id":"fa53cce7-ba71-0629-6a49-398a5bd1ac4f","name":"Note: Escalate Failure to Outlook"},{"parameters":{"content":"### Park in Dead-Letter Queue\n\ngoogleSheets — `append` operation against the connected account.\n\n↻ retries 3×/2s · 🔑 Google OAuth2 / service account","width":280,"height":232,"color":3},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote","typeVersion":1,"position":[9066,1540],"id":"4da286e7-8e5d-2426-8f2f-6477e037770e","name":"Note: Park in Dead-Letter Queue"},{"parameters":{"content":"# Approve expenses with Outlook and Notion on autopilot\n\n**Pattern:** Approval Workflow · **Level:** Architect · **Trigger:** Form\n\n## What it does\nApprove expenses with Outlook and Notion on autopilot. It starts from a hosted form submission.\n\n## Why it exists\nManual task routing is slow and error-prone; this workflow makes the process repeatable, monitored and hands-off, with failures surfaced instead of silently lost.\n\n## Main flow\nNew Task Form Submission → Keep Valid Tasks → Prepare Approval Packet → Request Approval via Slack → Hold for Decision → Approved? → Execute Approved Action (API) → …\n\n## Use it for\n- Teams that want to approval workflow without manual effort\n- Anyone automating task routing in software development\n- Replacing a fragile manual process with a reliable workflow\n\n## You get\n- Scales without extra headcount\n- Removes copy-paste errors\n- Keeps your systems in sync\n\n## Before first run\nConnect credentials: API key / bearer for the target API; Google OAuth2 / service account; Microsoft OAuth2; Notion integration token; Slack OAuth2.\nFollow the color key: 🟦 entry · 🟪 AI · 🟫 actions · ⬜ utilities · 🟩 outputs · 🟥 error rail.\nEach node has its own doc card underneath — read those before editing.","width":480,"height":900},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote","typeVersion":1,"position":[-830,80],"id":"771e6177-67d9-15b4-e1d8-11126e2d87e6","name":"📘 Workflow Overview"},{"parameters":{"content":"## 🛟 Error handling & retries\n\nExternal calls retry **3× with 2s backoff**. Anything still failing exits through its node's error output into the red error rail → context is captured and the on-call channel is alerted. Failures are also parked in a dead-letter queue for replay. Set an n8n **Error Workflow** in settings as the final safety net.","width":360,"height":260,"color":3},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote","typeVersion":1,"position":[-230,-260],"id":"ec443423-97b1-1dc0-33a7-b26b9a3226a1","name":"🛟 Error handling & retries"},{"parameters":{"content":"## ⏱ Rate limiting\n\nWork is batched and spaced with Wait so provider quotas aren't tripped. If you hit 429s, lower the batch size or raise the wait — throughput drops, reliability rises.","width":360,"height":260,"color":1},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote","typeVersion":1,"position":[190,-260],"id":"7d119bf2-a007-8c26-1359-d7968c369045","name":"⏱ Rate limiting"},{"parameters":{"content":"## 🙋 Human in the loop\n\nThe workflow pauses at the Wait node until a human posts a decision to the resume URL (included in the approval message). Approve → the action executes; anything else → recorded as declined. No timeout is set by default — add one under the Wait node's options if approvals go stale.","width":360,"height":260,"color":1},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote","typeVersion":1,"position":[610,-260],"id":"18103497-d22b-f0bb-4e7e-064ab90fe72d","name":"🙋 Human in the loop"},{"parameters":{"content":"## 🛠 Customize me\n\nQuick wins: point the data nodes at your own accounts (see 🔑 lines on each card), adjust the trigger cadence, and tune thresholds/labels to your task routing process. Every node card explains its role — safe to extend at any marked branch.","width":360,"height":260,"color":4},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote","typeVersion":1,"position":[1030,-260],"id":"95c59645-e78a-a40f-4c69-51270b5f004c","name":"🛠 Customize me"}],"connections":{"New Task Form Submission":{"main":[[{"node":"Keep Valid Tasks","type":"main","index":0}]]},"Keep Valid Tasks":{"main":[[{"node":"Prepare Approval Packet","type":"main","index":0}]]},"Prepare Approval Packet":{"main":[[{"node":"Request Approval via Slack","type":"main","index":0}]]},"Request Approval via Slack":{"main":[[{"node":"Hold for Decision","type":"main","index":0}],[{"node":"Capture Failure Context","type":"main","index":0}]]},"Hold for Decision":{"main":[[{"node":"Approved?","type":"main","index":0}]]},"Approved?":{"main":[[{"node":"Execute Approved Action (API)","type":"main","index":0}],[{"node":"Record Decline + Notify Requester","type":"main","index":0}]]},"Execute Approved Action (API)":{"main":[[{"node":"Join Decision Paths","type":"main","index":0}],[{"node":"Capture Failure Context","type":"main","index":0}]]},"Record Decline + Notify Requester":{"main":[[{"node":"Join Decision Paths","type":"main","index":1}],[{"node":"Capture Failure Context","type":"main","index":0}]]},"Join Decision Paths":{"main":[[{"node":"Fingerprint for Idempotency","type":"main","index":0}]]},"Fingerprint for Idempotency":{"main":[[{"node":"Drop Already-Processed Items","type":"main","index":0}]]},"Drop Already-Processed Items":{"main":[[{"node":"Offload to Post-Process Sub-workflow","type":"main","index":0}]]},"Offload to Post-Process Sub-workflow":{"main":[[{"node":"Record Sub-workflow Result","type":"main","index":0}],[{"node":"Capture Failure Context","type":"main","index":0}]]},"Record Sub-workflow Result":{"main":[[{"node":"Stamp Completion Time","type":"main","index":0}]]},"Stamp Completion Time":{"main":[[{"node":"Persist Run Metadata","type":"main","index":0}]]},"Persist Run Metadata":{"main":[[{"node":"Enrich with Reference Data","type":"main","index":0}]]},"Enrich with Reference Data":{"main":[[{"node":"Fold In Enrichment Fields","type":"main","index":0}],[{"node":"Capture Failure Context","type":"main","index":0}]]},"Fold In Enrichment Fields":{"main":[[{"node":"Load Previous Snapshot","type":"main","index":0}]]},"Load Previous Snapshot":{"main":[[{"node":"Compute Drift vs Snapshot","type":"main","index":0}],[{"node":"Capture Failure Context","type":"main","index":0}]]},"Compute Drift vs Snapshot":{"main":[[{"node":"Serialize Run Output (CSV)","type":"main","index":0}]]},"Serialize Run Output (CSV)":{"main":[[{"node":"Archive Row Snapshot","type":"main","index":0}]]},"Archive Row Snapshot":{"main":[[{"node":"Tag Pipeline Metadata","type":"main","index":0}],[{"node":"Capture Failure Context","type":"main","index":0}]]},"Tag Pipeline Metadata":{"main":[[{"node":"Guard Non-Empty title","type":"main","index":0}]]},"Guard Non-Empty title":{"main":[[{"node":"Cap Batch Volume","type":"main","index":0}]]},"Cap Batch Volume":{"main":[[{"node":"Summarize Run Stats","type":"main","index":0}]]},"Summarize Run Stats":{"main":[[{"node":"Append Audit Row (Google Sheets)","type":"main","index":0}]]},"Append Audit Row (Google Sheets)":{"main":[[{"node":"Send Summary to Slack","type":"main","index":0}],[{"node":"Capture Failure Context","type":"main","index":0}]]},"Capture Failure Context":{"main":[[{"node":"Escalate Failure to Outlook","type":"main","index":0}]]},"Escalate Failure to Outlook":{"main":[[{"node":"Park in Dead-Letter Queue","type":"main","index":0}]]},"Send Summary to Slack":{"main":[[],[{"node":"Capture Failure Context","type":"main","index":0}]]}},"active":false,"settings":{"executionOrder":"v1"},"meta":{"templateCredsSetupCompleted":false},"tags":[],"pinData":{},"versionId":"e832df16-04cd-4492-b95d-414a95dcc30d","id":"FDX08451"}